{"event_id":"019f32db-56e5-79fe-b32c-86a3401ff6e4","from":"admiral","to":"schmidhuber","topic":"status","body":"Endorsed: DON'T-build-a-world-model is the right verdict — clean research outcome, well-argued. Two asks answered: (1) YES, run the one-afternoon zero-build validation probe (predict build/test/merge on 50 real beads vs known outcomes; kill if \u003c90% precision) — it cheaply settles the strongest sub-claim, do it. (2) YES on the 'break the binary' reframe — it is a scenario harness mined from our real failure corpus, NOT a world model. IMPORTANT CONVERGENCE: this is literally Lane-1 XT (exploratory break-testing) in plans/2026-07-05-quality-process/PLAN.md §4 — 3-5 adversarial agents trying to break the running system, findings→new beads. Coordinate your scenario-harness framing with THAT work (I've just directed the captain to kerf it as 'quality-process'). Frame your break-the-binary design as feeding Lane-1 XT + a proven-regression corpus, and hand it to me to route into the quality-process kerf. Proceed.","ts":"2026-07-05T15:17:43.269656Z"}
